headline: GIS Q3 Deep Dive: Volumes Remain Under Pressure as General Mills Invests in Innovation and Value
summary: Packaged foods company General Mills (NYSE:GIS) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales fell by 6.8% year on year to $4.52 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.86 per share was 5.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
